Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.79,0:03:16.50,Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Moritaka, Takagi-kun is here to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.53,0:03:18.34,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.34,0:03:19.67,Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Please hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.51,0:03:26.18,Main,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:29.60,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So annoying.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.23,0:03:32.89,Main,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Saikou.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.91,0:03:36.65,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't call me "Saikou" or suddenly show up to meet me in the morning like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:40.65,Main,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, I'll call you Saikou and you can call me Shuuto.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.86,0:03:44.03,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,A Moritaka going by "Saikou",
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.86,0:03:44.03,TL Notes,TL Note,0000,0000,0000,,Note: The name "Moritaka" uses the same kanji as "Saikou" (最高), meaning "the best".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.03,0:03:46.58,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and an Akito going by "Shuuto" are a bit different.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.03,0:03:46.58,TL Notes,,0000,0000,0000,,The kanji for "Akito" (秋人) can also be pronounced "Shuuto", as in the English "shoot".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.87,0:03:48.70,Main,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? How are they different?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.91,0:03:53.04,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,The name "Shuuto" gives off a cool soccer image.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.54,0:03:55.21,Up Main,On-Screen Shouts,0000,0000,0000,,Saikou!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:56.33,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,"Saikou" sounds like I'm being made fun of.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:03:59.17,Main,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.21,0:04:00.34,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:02.80,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm gonna call you Shuujin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:02.80,TL Notes,TL Note,0000,0000,0000,,"Shuujin" is a Japanese word for "prisoner."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.80,0:04:05.34,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Shuujin?! Like a criminal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:08.05,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, isn't it? Akito can be read that way too, can't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.05,0:04:09.68,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Shuujin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.06,0:04:12.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Then, at least as Shuujin...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.23,0:04:14.38,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:15.98,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.15,0:04:20.86,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Your uncle died three years ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.15,0:04:23.65,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Did you check up on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.65,0:04:26.36,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We're neighbors. My parents knew. {QC - Perhaps 'We were neighbors' as I'm not sure whether he's referring to the fact that he was neighbors with his uncle, or whether he's neighbors with Moritaka}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.62,0:04:31.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,But they didn't know he was the mangaka, Kawaguchi Tarou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.64,0:04:32.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It is a pen name after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.54,0:04:35.71,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,His real name was Mashiro Nobuhiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.71,0:04:39.34,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like it just said "Mangaka dies" in the corner of some newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.46,0:04:43.59,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,If a mangaka can't get serialized, they're just a NEET.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.46,0:04:43.59,TL Notes,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Note: NEET stands for "Not in Education, Employment or Training"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.59,0:04:47.34,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,After being a NEET for seven years in a row, it'd be no surprise that you wanted to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:50.18,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,He committed suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.18,0:04:52.26,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,My parents said he died because he was overworked,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.26,0:04:54.89,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but he barely had any work for seven years, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.03,0:05:04.78,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,So, do you wanna give up on being a mangaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.78,0:05:07.57,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you quit, I'm gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.51,0:05:17.32,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna do it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.32,0:05:20.65,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Teamed up with you, we'll be the top mangakas in Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.65,0:05:23.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, I haven't decided if I'm teaming up with you or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.09,0:05:24.46,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.71,0:05:27.26,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who inspired you to do it in the first place, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.22,0:05:30.14,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't you, it was {\i1}Azuki{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:32.14,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? What's with that attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.14,0:05:35.23,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But you have my thanks, cupid Shuujin-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.73,0:05:41.23,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, Saikou, let's work together eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.24,0:05:42.02,Main,Iwase,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.57,0:05:45.61,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Iwase?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:49.78,Main,Iwase,0000,0000,0000,,How are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.91,0:05:52.83,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Well... Same as always, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.83,0:05:55.95,Main,Iwase,0000,0000,0000,,You can say that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.95,0:05:57.87,Main,Iwase,0000,0000,0000,,I won't lose to you on today's test.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.56,0:06:03.37,Main,Iwase,0000,0000,0000,,Even the results for the first term of third year will have a big impact on our high school applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.37,0:06:04.20,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:05.84,Main,Iwase,0000,0000,0000,,Have you decided which high school to go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.46,0:06:08.05,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.05,0:06:09.90,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So these two are the top of our grade?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.90,0:06:13.05,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, tests are such downers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.35,0:06:17.18,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, I just gave up and went to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:19.35,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I got my skin all shiny for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.35,0:06:21.06,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay, Kaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.06,0:06:23.65,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't get much studying done yesterday either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.65,0:06:24.89,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.89,0:06:27.55,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,You always get good scores anyhow, Miho.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.55,0:06:29.15,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,I do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.66,0:06:32.73,Main,Iwase,0000,0000,0000,,Bye then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:41.81,Main,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, settle down and write.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.29,0:06:43.71,Main,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Especially you, Suzuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.71,0:06:45.71,Main,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,At least try not to spell your name wrong.
